{
  "stem": "1415.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And as-- as Saturday morning came, my arm became swollen.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And my father, being a very, very religious man, he never-- he never-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what would that word be-- the-- like you'd desecrated the Shabbos.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he-- he took me to the hospital and they took some kind of X-rays, and they gave my-- my father a diagnosis that I had sclerosis of the bones.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Well, it was Tisha B'Av in our family, which means it's a-- it's a-- Tisha B'Av is a very sad day when our temple was destroyed.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So it was very sad in our home.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "After the Shabbat was over, my father took me in a-- in a-- cart to the next town, where, for the first time in my memory, I met my other grandfather and grandmother [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] in-- in Opatow, which was a town not too far from us.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "I would say several kilometers from our-- from Ostrowiec.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I got a chance to meet my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "She was a little tiny woman, even in my memory, because my grandfather was very, very tall.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "Even for today's generation, he would have been considered tall.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they all got around, the family, and decided that I should be taken to Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And it seems if, through a family, somebody that knew the doctor, who was also related, and they took further tests and-- and determined that it was only a break.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] In the meantime, I forgot to tell you is that while the Shabbat was going on, my father took me to a feldsher.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Now, a feldsher is-- is a practitioner.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "It's not a doctor.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "It's a practitioner.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he started to move my arm to try to settle it.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
